CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 25, 1963, pg. 2 reads: " Plan Rally - The planning committee for the big NAACP Centennial Rally, to be held Sunday, June 9, from 4 to 6 P.M., in Civic Arena, is shown as it went over final plans this week. Left to right, around  the table, are Byrd Brown, Mrs. Aldora S. Frazier, Harriette McCray, the Rev. R.C. Eberhardt, the Rev. Herbert Wilkerman, Lorende Tyler, Justin M. Johnson, E. Josephine Martin, Dorothy K. Williams, Fay Adams, Stanton Hammon and Mrs. Sarah Robinson. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fay Adams, Rev. R. C. Eberhardt, and Lorende Tyler seated at table for NAACP Centennial rally meeting
